post_text: Students who are interested in taking the AH only SAT exam being offered September 23 and October 14 must register using the form posted on Class of 2021, 2022 Classrooms. Students who are registered for the national testing dates are NOT automatically registered for these exam dates. Completing the form and submitting payment to AHSD is the only way students can register for the exam. Senior students will be given preference, but underclassmen can register and take the exam depending on how many seniors register for the exam. Parents seeking refunds for cancelled SAT dates should contact College Board directly.

Any senior student who is interested in learning more about Johnson College's Fast Track program can attend this zoom informational session. Parents are welcome and encouraged to attend. This program is for students who wish to earn credits toward a degree in either welding or building technology. The building technology program students choose a specific path, HVAC, carpentry, or electrical, the following year. Abington Heights provides funding for this program, so this is a great opportunity for senior students interested in the trades.

shared_text:
Abington Heights School Counselors
July 7 at 10:24 AM ·

IMPORTANT INFORMATION ON THE UPCOMING ACT:

Students and Parents/Guardians:

Unfortunately, a decision has been made to cancel the July 18 ACT out of an abundance of caution for the safety of your students and your families. The majority of test takers registered were from out of state and your students' safety is our top priority.

With the backlog of test-takers looking for a test site, it is in your best interest to consider BOTH the ACT and the SAT and start looking at available dates and sites.

AH is scheduled to hold the August, September and October SAT and the September ACT.

The roster for the July ACT was made up of mostly out of state students coming from NY, NJ, CT and even FL, so you need to stay ahead of the large number of students requesting a small number of seats.

Abington Heights Music Department
May 12 at 9:17 PM ·

A very special congratulations to Emily Harris and Dylan Cummings for being accepted to compete in the PMEA Region 4 Band Festival that was supposed to be held at Honesdale High School this season. Due to covid-19, the festival was cancelled. We continued to hold video auditions for acceptance into the All-State ensembles. The PMEA All-State Convention was to be held at Kalahari this season, but it was cancelled as well. Emily and Dylan both submitted exceptional virtual auditions! Stay tuned for results! I am so very proud of these incredible musicians, and I am blessed to have been able to work with them since they began their instrumental journeys in middle school.
text:
Abington Heights Music Department
May 12 at 9:17 PM ·

A very special congratulations to Emily Harris and Dylan Cummings for being accepted to compete in the PMEA Region 4 Band Festival that was supposed to be held at Honesdale High School this season. Due to covid-19, the festival was cancelled. We continued to hold video auditions for acceptance into the All-State ensembles. The PMEA All-State Convention was to be held at Kalahari this season, but it was cancelled as well. Emily and Dylan both submitted exceptional virtual auditions! Stay tuned for results! I am so very proud of these incredible musicians, and I am blessed to have been able to work with them since they began their instrumental journeys in middle school.

Abington Heights Music Department is at Abington HeightsHigh School.
May 13 at 7:54 AM · Clarks Summit, PA ·

The Abington Heights Music Department would like to recognize all of our senior members and thank each and every one of them for their hard work and dedication to the Abington Heights Music Department! We have been blessed and honored to have them all as students! We will be posting a different senior a day, please like, share and congratulate them on a job well done! Today’s senior is: Alex Thornton! Alex plans on continuing her academic career at Keystone College and will be majoring in Environmental Biology. Alex is a member of the Abington Heights Concert Band, Jazz Band and Marching Band!
#cometproud #leadingtheway #seniorsrock

The Abington Heights Music Department would like to recognize all of our senior members and thank each and every one of them for their hard work and dedication to the Abington Heights Music Department! We have been blessed and honored to have them all as students! We will be posting a different senior a day, please like, share and congratulate them on a job well done! Today’s senior is: Makenzie Allred!! Makenzie plans on continuing her academic career at Northeastern University and majoring in biochemistry and Chemical Engineering. Makenzie is a member of the Abington Heights Concert Band, Jazz Band, Marching Band and Symphony Orchestra.
#cometproud #leadingtheway #seniorsrock

post_text:
Any AP students who have not submitted their AP balances should do so right away. Checks should be mailed to the Abington Heights Administration Bldg, 200 E Grove St.
If you have not paid your balance, this will not affect your ability to take your AP exam(s) next week. However, unpaid balances will be an obligation that could affect your ability to receive your diploma or register for a parking pass for next year. Good luck on your exams!!

Celebrating AHHS Class of 2020 Track and Field Athletes...congratulations and best of luck to each and every one of you!!

Noah Bolus, Cole Capwell, Joe Danoski, Robert Horvath, Sean Kane, Matthew Kelleher, Nick Klapatch, James Lefchack, Damon Martin, Shervin Mokhtari, Corey Perkins, Michael Pusateri, Christian Ragnacci, Carson Smith, Ian Stanton, Sam Kalmanowicz, Sadie Henzes, Adele Hollander, Rachel Klein, Anna Marchetta, Kate Chickillo, Alexandra Thornton

"Friendships born on the field of athletic strife are the real gold of competition. Awards become corroded, friends gather no dust.”
- Jesse Owens

April 28 at 7:45 AM · Clarks Summit, PA ·

The Abington Heights Music Department would like to recognize all of our senior members and thank each and every one of them for their hard work and dedication to the Abington Heights Music Department! We have been blessed and honored to have them all as students! We will be posting a different senior a day, please like, share and congratulate them on a job well done! Today’s senior is: Lucy Earl!! Lucy plans on continuing her academic career and majoring in environmental science. Lucy is a member of the Abington Heights Honors Choir!
#cometproud #leadingtheway #seniorsrock

Hey Comet Nation! During the Covid-19 lock down, the Athletic department has been working to collect information about our illustrious history. You are asked to help! Please review our records pages, if you have documentation that will help us add to these documents please share them with us in the Google Form. Information we are seeking will include coaches names, team records, team accomplishments, and individual accomplishments. Individual accomplishments will include record performances, milestones, district/league/state champions, 1st team all-star/all-regional/all-state. We will continune to update the information as it is sent to us. Thank you for your assistance.

Go Comets!

post_text: Seniors Daniel Cummins and Nina Sampogne have advanced as Regional Finalists in the Coca-Cola Scholars Program. Nearly 200,000 students applied for this prestigious scholarship. Daniel and Nina advanced to the group of 1900 Semifinalists and were recently notified that have advanced to the Regional Finalist Phase, which includes 251 students. The Coca-Cola Scholars Foundation offers college scholarships to exceptional High School students dedicated to academics, leadership, service and action that positively affects others. Daniel and Nina interviewed with the Coca-Cola Board in Philadelphia last Saturday, hoping to become one of the 125 Finalists, which will each receive a $20,000 college scholarship. Good luck to both of these great students!

post_text:
On Saturday February 22, 2020 at Parkland High School the Abington Heights boys powerlifting team captured first place in the 5A-4A division of the Pennsylvania State Teenage Powerlifting Championship over runner up Kennard-Dale High School. Team members are: Zach Bator, Christian Lezinski, Will Stevens, Casey Knott, Corey Tokash, Brandon Lezinski, Caleb White, Caden Casal, Jared White, Jacob Mann, Brock Pentasuglio, Bodie LaCoe, Dominic Peters and Myles Knott.
The team was lead by USA Team member Bodie LaCoe. Bodie received the “Jeff Moyer” award that is presented to a outstanding lifter that exhibits sportsmanship and excellent lifting.

The Abington Heights girls team earned the second place team award at the same competition, behind champion Kennard-Dale High School. Team members are: Kaylee Mann, Olivia Lam, Kate O’Brien, Lindsey James, Ayana Rivera , Rachel Klein and Mallory Knott. The team was lead by Rachel Klein that is also a USA Team member.

Parkland High School won the 6A division and Jim Thorpe High School captured the 3A-1A division.

Congratulations!!!

shared_text:
Abington Heights Music Department
February 4 at 3:40 PM ·

This past weekend 23 talented ladies from the Abington Heights High School Concert Choir participated in the High Voice Festival at Penn State Main University under the direction of Jayne Glocke! We spent the day working at a college level with the Oriana Singers and 180 high school girls from across the state and bordering states.
It was wonderful meeting and working with new colleagues. I want to congratulate Penn State for offering an opportunity to provide irreplaceable musical opportunities and developmental opportunities to our students. The girls met new friends, enjoyed Penn State Creamery, and participated in a college concert all in one day! #forwardthinking #cometproud

post_text: On February 1 st, the AHSO Team attend the Yale University Science Olympiad Invitational in New Haven, CT. Students competed against 40 other high school teams in 23 different STEM events and medaled in Experimental Design, Fossils, Gravity Vehicle and Ornithology. Congrats Braeden Mathers, Josh Parfrey, Ryan Salony, Rory Harris, Jakob Quanbeck, Hanna White, Leah Ludwikowski, Lydia Hodge, Jenna Patel, Faatihah Nayeem, Alex Thornton, Sarah Siddiqui and Gavin Ross. We are Comet Proud!!

The following members of the AH Powerlifting Team competed in the USAPL High School Powerlifting Meet on Sunday, January 26. Eleven members of the team qualified to compete in the National High School Championship to be held in Texas during March 26-29. Meet results;

Ayana Rivera 103, 1st 9-10 grade; Rachel Klein 103, 1st 11-12 grade; Lindsey James 123, 1st 9-10 grade; Olivia Lam 138, 1st 9-10 grade; Kate O’Brien 138, 3rd 9-10 grade; Bodie LaCoe 116, 1st 11-12 grade and meet outstanding lifter; Jared White 145, 1st 9-10 grade; Jacob Mann 145, 2nd 9-10 grade, Sean Kane 163, 1st 11-12 grade; Caden Casal 182, 2nd 9-10 grade; Casey Knott 182, 1st 11-12 grade and Christian Lezinski 260, 1st 9-10 grade.
